input: Bob is smart. Charlie is young. Erin is furry. Erin is quiet. Erin is smart. Erin is young. Fiona is quiet. Nice, smart things are quiet. All green things are quiet. If something is red then it is furry. All smart things are furry. If Bob is furry and Bob is smart then Bob is red. Quiet things are young. If something is red then it is nice. Question: Bob is young.?
output:
universe u

constant obj : Type u

constant Bob : obj
constant Charlie : obj
constant Erin : obj
constant Fiona : obj

constant Smart : obj → Prop
constant Young : obj → Prop
constant Furry : obj → Prop
constant Quiet : obj → Prop
constant Nice : obj → Prop
constant Red : obj → Prop
constant Green : obj → Prop

axiom T1 : Smart Bob
axiom T2 : Young Charlie
axiom T3 : Furry Erin
axiom T4 : Quiet Erin
axiom T5 : Smart Erin
axiom T6 : Young Erin
axiom T7 : Quiet Fiona

axiom R1 : ∀ x : obj, Nice x ∧ Smart x → Quiet x
axiom R2 : ∀ x : obj, Green x → Quiet x
axiom R3 : ∀ x : obj, Red x → Furry x
axiom R4 : ∀ x : obj, Smart x → Furry x
axiom R5 : Furry Bob ∧ Smart Bob → Red Bob
axiom R6 : ∀ x : obj, Quiet x → Young x
axiom R7 : ∀ x : obj, Red x → Nice x

theorem bob_is_young : Young Bob :=
begin
  apply R6,
  apply R1,
  split,
  apply R7,
  apply R5,
  split,
  apply R4,
  exact T1,
  exact T1,
end

-- The answer is True
